tafsir[13]{c,v,t}:
  53,45,"And that He created the two types: Male and female."
  53,46,"From a drop when it is placed in the womb."
  53,47,"And that He will undertake to recreate them after they die for the resurrection."
  53,48,"And that He enriches whichever of His servants He wills by making him the owner of wealth and He gives wealth that people take as possessions they acquire."
  53,53,"He raised the villages of the people of Lot to the sky and then dropped them to ground."
  53,54,"He then covered them with stones after raising them to the sky and dropping them to the ground."
  53,56,"This messenger that is sent to you is from the class of the earlier messengers."
  53,57,"The Day of Standing has drawn nearer."
  53,58,"There is no one that can push it back and no one to uncover it besides Allah."
  53,60,"And laugh mockingly at it and not cry when hearing its admonitions?"
  54,2,"When the idolaters see any sign or proof of the truthfulness of the Prophet (peace be upon him) they turn away from accepting it and say: The evidence and proof we have seen are false sorcery."
  54,4,"There has come to them reports of the nations that Allah destroyed because of their disbelief and wrongdoing that were sufficient to deter them from their disbelief and wrongdoing."
  54,5,"What has come to them is complete wisdom to establish the evidence against them. The warnings do not benefit a people who do not have faith in Allah and nor in the last day."